message.content:
This command establishes an SSH (Secure Shell) connection to a remote server with the specified IP address, port number, and user name "user". The "-i" option specifies the path to the private key file used for authentication. In this case, it is pointing to UserKey.pem in the home directory of the user running the command.
The "-C" option tells ssh to use a channel mode (SSH_CONNECT) instead of an anonymous mode (SSH_AUTH). The "25900:localhost:5900" part specifies that the remote server is located at 25900 port 5900 on localhost, which should be your own machine.
The "-L" option tells ssh to use a large key size for the private key file (1024 bits), and it also sets the maximum number of failed login attempts before disconnecting from the connection. In this case, it is set to 25900.
